article.headline: Princeton 62, Yale 54
article.story: PRINCETON, N.J. -- Dan Mavraides scored 16 points and pulled down six rebounds to lead Princeton to a 62-54 win over Yale on Saturday night. Douglas Davis added 12 points for the Tigers (12-12, 7-4 Ivy League), who shot 53.5 percent from the field. Alex Zampier had 19 points for the Bulldogs (12-14, 7-5), while Ross Morin added 16. Princeton took command early on, jumping out to a 14-0 lead, but Yale responded with a 13-0 run that featured two 3-pointers by Zampier. The teams then traded baskets for the rest of the half, with the Tigers ahead 27-20 at the break. Princeton then maintained a slim lead throughout the second half, holding off several Bulldog rallies before finally pulling away in the closing minutes.
